{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The test results do not prove that Jesus had a wife, only that the fragment of papyrus with the phrase, \u201cJesus said to them, \u2018My wife,\u2019\u201d is most likely not a forgery.", "abstract": "Dr Karen L King study in the Harvard Theological Review concludes that controversial 'Gospel of Jesus's Wife' is not a modern forgery, and that ink and papyrus involved are likely to be ancient; fragment caused uproar after being unveiled in 2012 because it made reference not only to Jesus having a wife, but to her being a disciple.", "section_name": "Science", "print_page": "12", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Laurie", "role": "reported", "lastname": "GOODSTEIN", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By LAURIE GOODSTEIN", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/04/10/science/scrap-of-papyrus-referring-to-jesus-wife-is-likely-to-be-ancient-scientists-say.html", "lead_paragraph": "The test results do not prove that Jesus had a wife, only that the fragment of papyrus with the phrase, \u201cJesus said to them, \u2018My wife,\u2019\u201d is most likely not a forgery.", "headline": {"main": "Papyrus Referring to Jesus\u2019 Wife Is More Likely Ancient Than Fake, Scientists Say", "print_headline": "Papyrus Referring to Jesus\u2019 Wife Is More Likely Ancient Than Fake, Scientists Say"}, "_id": "53466c2238f0d84cf0cad531", "word_count": "810", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/04/10/us/jesus/jesus-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/04/10/us/jesus/jesus-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 322, "url": "images/2014/04/10/us/jesus/jesus-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/04/10/us/jesus/jesus-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "322"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/04/10/us